text: Corinne Conley (born May 23, 1929) is an American-Canadian actress. She was born in New York City. Her career began in 1953. She played Phyllis Anderson on the NBC-TV daytime drama Days of Our Lives. She played the female lead in CBC-TV's adaptation of the soap opera Search for Tomorrow. ==References== Category:1929 births Category:Living people Category:American movie actors Category:American television actors Category:American stage actors Category:American voice actors Category:Naturalized citizens of Canada Category:Canadian movie actors Category:Canadian television actors Category:Canadian stage actors Category:Canadian voice actors Category:Actors from New York City Category:Actors from Ottawa
